# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js already has full model infrastructure for image-text-to-text models
(`AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `imageTextToTextForward`, 11 registered model families
like SmolVLM, Qwen2-VL, LLaVA, PaliGemma, Florence2). What is missing is the
**pipeline layer**: no `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class exists, the task is not in
`SUPPORTED_TASKS`, and `AutoModelForImageTextToText` is not imported in `pipelines.js`.

This plan adds those missing pieces to `src/pipelines.js` only — no other file needs
to change.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/pipelines.js` | **Only file to modify** — all 5 insertions go here |
| `src/models.js` (read-only) | `AutoModelForImageTextToText` exported at line 8736; `imageTextToTextForward` at line 813 |
| `src/models/idefics3/processing_idefics3.js` (read-only) | Signature: `_call(text, images)` — text first |
| `src/models/qwen2_vl/processing_qwen2_vl.js` (read-only) | Signature: `_call(text, images)` — text first |
| `src/models/llava/processing_llava.js` (read-only) | Signature: `_call(images, text)` — images first ⚠️ |
| `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_to_text.js` (read-only) | Reference for test structure |

---

## Key Design Decisions

**Processor call convention — text first**
Different processors have inconsistent arg orders:
- Text first (modern): `Idefics3Processor`, `SmolVLMProcessor`, `Qwen2VLProcessor`
- Images first (older): `LlavaProcessor`, `PaliGemmaProcessor`, `Florence2Processor`

The pipeline uses `this.processor(texts, preparedImages)` (text first), consistent with
the modern convention and how Python's `ImageTextToTextPipeline` passes named kwargs
(`text=text, images=images`). LLaVA / PaliGemma / Florence2 users would need to call
the processor directly; this is a known limitation to document in the JSDoc.

**Single processor call for all images, not a per-image loop**
Unlike `ImageToTextPipeline` (which loops one image at a time), this pipeline calls the
processor once with all texts + all images. VLM processors perform joint tokenization
(expanding image tokens in text to match patch counts), so images cannot be processed
independently from their paired text.

**Prompt stripping**
VLMs are decoder-only: `generate()` returns the full sequence (prompt + generated). We
strip the prompt portion using character-length subtraction on the decoded text:
1. `batch_decode(inputs.input_ids, { skip_special_tokens: true })` → prompt text (image
   tokens stripped as special tokens)
2. `batch_decode(outputTokenIds, { skip_special_tokens: true })` → full text (same strip)
3. Slice: `fullText.slice(promptText.length).trim()` → generated text only

**Output format — matches `ImageToTextPipeline`**
- Non-batched single image: returns `[{ generated_text: "..." }]`
- Batched N images: returns `[[{ generated_text: "..." }], ...]` (N arrays)
- Supports `num_return_sequences > 1` via grouping logic

---

## Implementation Steps

All 5 steps modify only `src/pipelines.js`.

---

### Step 1 — Add import (line ~33)

